RANGERS bosses today revealed they have reached an out of court settlement with ex-director Imran Ahamd. Rangers reach out of court settlement with ex-director RANGERS bosses today revealed they have reached an out of court settlement with ex-director Imran Ahamd.In a statement to the London Stock Exchange, the club confirmed the deal and said the amount given was &quot;significantly less&quot; than the &pound;620,000 previously ring-fenced by court at Ahmad's request.The former commercial director said he was owed &pound;500,000 for an unpaid bonus and another &pound;120,000 for legal costs. 